# Next.js App Router Rules

## Page Files — Always Thin (≤ 15 lines)

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — page.tsx
import LeadsTable from "@/src/modules/admin/leads/components/LeadsTable";
export const metadata = { title: "Inquiries — Zafora Admin" };
export default function LeadsPage() { return <LeadsTable />; }

// ❌ WRONG — business logic in page
export default function LeadsPage() {
  const [data, setData] = useState([]); // Never
  useEffect(() => fetch(...), []); // Never
}
```

## Server vs Client Components

| Data pattern | Use |
|-------------|-----|
| Public page data | Server Component — `async` function, `await apiClient()` |
| Admin interactive data | `"use client"` + `useQuery` via `apiAxios` |
| Form submission | Server Action in `lib/actions/public.ts` or `lib/actions/admin.ts` |
| Modal / drawer | `"use client"` island |

## "use client" Rules

- Only add to components that need: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useQuery`, event handlers
- Never add to full `page.tsx` — use client islands inside server pages
- Never fetch with `apiAxios` in a Server Component — use `apiClient` instead

## Auth Guard Pattern

```
middleware.ts          → blocks /admin/* (except /login) if no access_token cookie
(admin)/layout.tsx     → calls requireAdmin() — throws redirect if invalid
lib/actions/admin.ts   → every Server Action calls requireAdmin() first
```

## Route Constants — Always Use

```ts
import { ROUTES } from "@/src/lib/url-helpers";
// ROUTES.ADMIN.LEADS, ROUTES.ADMIN.PROJECTS, ROUTES.LOGIN, etc.
// Never: router.push("/admin/leads") — always: router.push(ROUTES.ADMIN.LEADS)
```

## Metadata

```tsx
// Per page — never document.title or next/head
export const metadata = { title: "Projects — Zafora Admin" };
// Dynamic:
export async function generateMetadata({ params }) { ... }
```

## Forbidden Patterns

- ❌ `pages/` directory, `getServerSideProps`, `getStaticProps`
- ❌ `next/head` for SEO
- ❌ `<a href="/admin/leads">` — use `<Link href={ROUTES.ADMIN.LEADS}>`
- ❌ `<img src="...">` — use `<Image>` from `next/image`
- ❌ Raw `fetch()` in client components — use `apiAxios`
